cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is about using reinforcement learning to train neural network policies for robotic skills, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for policy representation also relates to computer vision (cs.CV), as visual perception is often a key component of robotic tasks. Finally, the paper discusses the sharing of robot-specific information, such as dynamics and kinematics, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
